	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Type: class_usage_effectivity_context_item 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_item"/>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Type: effectivity_for_replacement 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.effectivity_for_replacement"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.effectivity_for_replacement"/>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Entity: class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment  
   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment">
A <b>class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment</b> is a type of <express_extref linkend="effectivity_context_assignment" standard="management_resources_schema"/> that assigns an <express_extref linkend="applied_effectivity_assignment" standard="automotive_design"/> specifying the "effectivity items" that impact the design of a solution for an "effectivity context item". 
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Entity: class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment  Attribute: items 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment.items"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment.items">
the set of items for which the <express_extref linkend="applied_effectivity_assignment" standard="automotive_design"/> identifies a design impact.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Entity: class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment.wr:WR1">
The <b>class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment</b> shall have a role with a name of 'class usage influence'.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Entity: class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment  Where: WR2 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment.wr:WR2"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment.wr:WR2">
The <b>class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment</b> shall only have instances of <express_extref linkend="product_definition" standard="management_resources_schema"/> in its set of items which reference as "frame of reference" a <express_extref linkend="product_definition_context" standard="management_resources_schema"/> with name 'conceptual definition'.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Entity: class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment  Where: WR3 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment.wr:WR3"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment.wr:WR3">
The <b>class_usage_effectivity_context_assignment</b> shall reference an <express_extref linkend="applied_effectivity_assignment" standard="automotive_design"/> with an "assigned effectivity" which is not of an effectivity subtype and which has an id of 'class usage' and which has only <express_extref linkend="product_concept_feature_category_usage" standard="automotive_design"/> objects in the set of items. 
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Rule: breakdown_element_requires_product_definition 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.breakdown_element_requires_product_definition"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.breakdown_element_requires_product_definition">
The <b>breakdown_element_requires_product_definition</b> rule constrains any instance of <express_extref linkend="product_definition_formation" standard="product_definition_schema"/> that represents a version of a functional element or of a physical element to have at least a corresponding definition.
</ext_description>
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.breakdown_element_requires_product_definition.wr:WR1">
Any <express_extref linkend="product_definition_formation" standard="product_definition_schema"/> that represents a version of a function element shall be referred by at least one "product definition" whose frame of reference name is 'functional definition'.
</ext_description>
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.breakdown_element_requires_product_definition.wr:WR2">
Any <express_extref linkend="product_definition_formation" standard="product_definition_schema"/> that represents a version of a physical element shall be referred by at least one "product definition" whose frame of reference name is 'conceptual definition'.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Rule: restrict_product_definitions_for_design_constraint_association 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.restrict_product_definitions_for_design_constraint_association"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.restrict_product_definitions_for_design_constraint_association">
The <b>restrict_product_definitions_for_design_constraint_association</b> rule constrains any instance of <express_extref linkend="product_definition_relationship" standard="product_definition_schema"/> of type 'design constraint association' to have:
<ul>
			<li>a "relating product definition" whose frame of reference name is 'design constraint definition';</li>
			<li>a "related product definition" whose frame of reference name is 'alternative definition' , 'functional definition' or 'conceptual definition'.</li>
		</ul>
	</ext_description>
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.restrict_product_definitions_for_design_constraint_association.wr:WR1">
There shall not be any instance of <express_extref linkend="product_definition_relationship" standard="product_definition_schema"/> of type 'design constraint association' that does not have:
<ul>
			<li>a "relating product definition" whose frame of reference name is 'design constraint definition', or,</li>
			<li>a "related product definition" whose frame of reference name is 'alternative definition' , 'functional definition' or 'conceptual definition'.</li>
		</ul>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Rule: constraint_definition_requires_constraint_category 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.constraint_definition_requires_constraint_category"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.constraint_definition_requires_constraint_category">
The <b>constraint_definition_requires_constraint_category</b> rule constrains any instance of <express_extref linkend="product_definition" standard="product_definition_schema"/> whose frame of reference name is 'design constraint definition', to be a definition of a product of category 'requirement'.
</ext_description>
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.constraint_definition_requires_constraint_category.wr:WR1">
There shall not be any instance of <express_extref linkend="product_definition" standard="product_definition_schema"/> whose frame of reference name is 'design constraint definition' and which is not a definition of a product of category 'requirement'.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Rule: design_constraint_requires_product_definition 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.design_constraint_requires_product_definition"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.design_constraint_requires_product_definition">
The <b>design_constraint_requires_product_definition</b> rule constrains any instance of <express_extref linkend="product_definition_formation" standard="product_definition_schema"/> of a product of category 'requirement' to have at least a corresponding definition.
</ext_description>
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.design_constraint_requires_product_definition.wr:WR1">
Any <express_extref linkend="product_definition_formation" standard="product_definition_schema"/> of a product of category 'requirement'  shall be referred by at least one "product definition" whose frame of reference name is 'design constraint definition'.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Rule: restrict_configuration_design_for_design_constraint 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_design_constraint"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_design_constraint">
The <b>restrict_configuration_design_for_design_constraint</b> constrains any instance of <express_extref linkend="configuration_design" standard="configuration_management_schema"/> that has a name 'design constraint usage' 
to refer with its design attribute to a <express_extref linkend="product_definition" standard="product_definition_schema"/> whose "frame of reference" name is 'design constraint definition'.
<note>This ensures that use <express_extref linkend="configuration_design" standard="configuration_management_schema"/> to represent a "Design constraint context association" is correct.</note>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Entity: restrict_configuration_design_for_design_constraint  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_design_constraint.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_design_constraint.wr:WR1">
There shall not be any instance of <express_extref linkend="configuration_design" standard="configuration_management_schema"/> that has a name 'design constraint usage',
that does not refer with its design attribute to a <express_extref linkend="product_definition" standard="product_definition_schema"/> whose "frame of reference" name is 'design constraint definition'.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Rule: restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association">
The <b>restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association</b> constrains any instance of <express_extref linkend="configuration_design" standard="configuration_management_schema"/> that has a name 'functionality'
to refer with its design attribute to a <express_extref linkend="product_definition" standard="product_definition_schema"/> whose "frame of reference" name is 'functional definition'.
<p>It also constrains any instance of <express_extref linkend="configuration_design" standard="configuration_management_schema"/> that has a name 'realization'
to refer with its design attribute to a <express_extref linkend="product_definition" standard="product_definition_schema"/> whose "frame of reference" name is 'conceptual definition'.
</p>
		<p>In both cases, the "item concept" indirectly referred to, shall be a <express_extref linkend="Product_class" standard="automotive_design"/>.
</p>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Entity: restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association  Where: WR1 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association.wr:WR1"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association.wr:WR1">
There shall not be any instance of <express_extref linkend="configuration_design" standard="configuration_management_schema"/> that has a name 'functionality'
that does not refer with its design attribute to a <express_extref linkend="product_definition" standard="product_definition_schema"/> whose "frame of reference" name is 'functional definition'.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Entity: restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association  Where: WR2 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association.wr:WR2"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association.wr:WR2">
There shall not be any instance of <express_extref linkend="configuration_design" standard="configuration_management_schema"/> that has a name 'realization'
that does not refer with its design attribute to a <express_extref linkend="product_definition" standard="product_definition_schema"/> whose "frame of reference" name is 'conceptual definition'.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Specification_control_mim  Entity: restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association  Where: WR3 
   <express_ref linkend="specification_control:mim:Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association.wr:WR3"/>

  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Specification_control_mim.restrict_configuration_design_for_class_breakdown_association.wr:WR3">
There shall not be any instance of <express_extref linkend="configuration_design" standard="configuration_management_schema"/> that has a name 'realization' or 'functionality', 
that does not indirectly refer to an "item concept" of type 
<express_extref linkend="Product_class" standard="automotive_design"/>.
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
